comment: To everyone mindlessly supporting Depp (similarly to how everyone rallied behind Amber a few months back): let the court decide. The version of events provided by the media doesn't necessarily match with reality and high profile celebrities more often than not have control over the narrative told by or available to the media. Also, this only the lawsuit against the Sun, not the lawsuit v Amber herself. We weren't there throughout their relationship and we haven't seen ALL the evidence provided by BOTH parties in each case (the fraction of evidence leaked to the press is most likely only a small portion of what was provided to the judge). So, there is no point in mindlessly mass-bullying eather side. Keep in mind that a lot of the leaks of the evidence to the press, have most likely been selectively leeked by the parties themselves to garner public support and also keep in mind that a lot of the "witnesses" on either side of this case are either financially or strongly personally connected to the applicant or the defendant. A best friend, employee or former lover might have incentives to align themselves with a version of events that does not actually match with what really happened. Neither Amber nor Johnny are guilty until a final ruling declares them to be, so this online witch hunt is totally unacceptable. You might be a fan of these celebrities, but they're actors for a reason: you have no clue how they would behave in real life.
